Package stocker.model.database

Class DatabaseModel

  • java.lang.Object
    • stocker.model.database.DatabaseObserverPattern
      • stocker.model.database.DatabaseModel
  • public class DatabaseModel
extends DatabaseObserverPattern
    The database model is responsible for holding and processing the stock related data. The model consists of 3 components, an observer pattern, DatabaseObserverPattern, implements 3 lists for 3 different observer types. A DatabaseStockListener listens to changes in the stock data. The DatabaseActionListener listens to active requests from the model for input and “subscribing” to stocks. And a DatabaseStatusListener observes status changes in the database, e.g. whether and to which server there is a connection. In addition, the database model implements a list of the StockData type and an assignment table HashMap <String, AlarmWrapper>. The StockData class has the function of dividing the stock data according to individual stocks. The key element, of the String type, of the allocation table stands for the “symbol” of the shares. The value element of the type AlarmWrapper has the function of summarizing and saving all alarms of a share. In addition, the database model contains various methods such as. Getter to access stocks and alarms under certain aspects. Setters and "Adder" to change the status of certain stocks or to add new data from the provider. Remover to delete stocks or alarms and other methods of notifying the observer.
    Author:
    Christoph Kaplan
